<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Tarkis on 11-26-2000 07:00 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Not trying to sound like a smug little s**t. But every one keeps saying NEW system. You "need to buy a new system to play".
Where is that? I don't see that. What I see is a 50 dollar video card. Maybe a 60 dollar overdrive.
I'm running a Generic Yamaha 3D sound card. (12 bucks)
400 Celeron (under 50 bucks)
96 Megs of ram (70 bucks or less now)
You don't need a NEW system. just some simple upgrades to your existing one. And if your machine is a bit older then most there are ways to get old hardware components out there for it to help it play EQ.
Also just a little FYI. Look at all the games slated to come out at the end of 2001 and early 2002. ALL are requiring 128 Megs of ram as minimum system requirements.
More CPU Speed. Something like a 500 or better.
Whether we like it or not we do have to keep up with advancing technology. It sucks I know. But if we didn't keep up we wouldn't have games like EQ.  :)

Tarkis</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
